	<div class = "idea">
		<h3>Shopping app/website</h3>
		<p>Develop an application where you can make a list of things you're planning to shop for and set up price alerts for those items. </p>
		<p>
			Important features:
			<ul>
				<li> Add webpage URLs to be parsed so that prices can be determined. </li>
				<li> Search products by UPC or keyword, aggregates hits on Amazon, Newegg, etc.
				</li>
				<li> Save searches and items on an easy-to-read interface, like a stock price app, to watch prices
				</li>
				<li>Set up price alerts when price drops past certain threshold. Maybe via email.</li>
				<li>Support searches on deal websites like slickdeals, edealinfo, etc</li>
				<li>Scrapes Craigslist data (might be against their TOS) </li>
			</ul>
			Not-so-important features:
			<ul>
				<li>Search forums and classifieds</li>
				<li> Chart or otherwise save historical prices since saving the search</li>
			</ul>
		</p>
	</div>
	
	<div class = "idea">
		<h3>Car Performance Data App (attached to Tom Zhang)</h3>
		<p>The Nissan GTR has a screen that plots lots of car data, like acceleration in every direction, speed, etc etc. I'd like to make an app that does the same thing, but for a smartphone or tablet. Additionally, it can have an "HUD mode" where it shows speed and heading and other stuff that BMW's HUD does. </p>
		<p>Important features:
			<ul>
				<li>Able to display current speed, heading, and acceleration</li>
				<li>Calibrate for different mounting orientations</li>
				<li>Tablet and phone versions</li>
				<li>Timer</li>
			</ul>
			Nice features:
			<ul>
				<li>Bluetooth integration to get OBD-II data with a thing like <a href="http://www.amazon.com/RioRand-Bluetooth-Diagnostic-Scanner-Android-compatible/dp/B004KL0I9I">this guy</a>.</li>
				<li>Chart various parameters over time</li>
				<li>GPS/mapping features (Map various parameters over location)</li>
				<li>GPS-integrated lap timer (Starts/stops when you pass a point)</li>
				<li>Basically any feature available on the <a href="http://www.autoblog.com/2013/06/06/bmw-readying-impressive-track-focused-m-power-app/">BMW M Power app</a></li>
			</ul>
			Hardware needed:
			<ul>
			<li>Android phone</li>
			<li>Android tablet (preferably 7")</li>
			<li>MAYBE iPhone/iPad mini; I'd like to focus on Android though.</li>
			<li>Some sort of non-derpy stable car phone mount</li>
			<li>Car (I can provide)</li>
			<li>OBD-II bluetooth adaptor (<a href="http://www.amazon.com/RioRand-Bluetooth-Diagnostic-Scanner-Android-compatible/dp/B004KL0I9I">like this one</a>) (Not necessarily that one though) (may need to homebrew one)</li>
			</ul>
		</p>
	</div>

